            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;The OP is asking to parse a very limited subset of XHTML: start tags. What makes (X)HTML a CFG is its potential to have elements between the start and end tags of other elements (as in a grammar rule &lt;code&gt;A -&amp;gt; s A e&lt;/code&gt;). (X)HTML does &lt;i&gt;not&lt;/i&gt; have this property &lt;i&gt;within&lt;/i&gt; a start tag: a start tag cannot contain other start tags. The subset that the OP is trying to parse is not a CFG.&lt;/span&gt;

